tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  20,100,"Whoever turns away from this Qur’ān which has been revealed to you and does not believe in it and act accordingly will come on the Day of Judgment carrying great sin and deserving a painful punishment."
  20,101,"Staying in this punishment forever. How awful a burden they will be carrying on the day of judgment."
  20,103,"They will talk to one another quietly saying: “You did not stay in the Transitory Stage after death except ten nights”."
  20,110,"Allah knows what people will face in the final hour and He knows what they will have left behind in their worldly life. All the servants together cannot encompass the knowledge of Allah’s being and His qualities."